@node "Requirements" "What you need to use it"

@{b}Requirements@{ub}
============

  - An Amiga
  - OS 2.0 or 2.1 if you want to use locale support
  - ReqTools library
  - and a Prelude soundcard with prelude.library installed

  Note: Because the prelude.library documentation is not finished yet
  and some functions are not usable as described in the docs, this program
  may not run under special conditions and all library versions.
  I will do my very best to update PrlMixerMUI if the library doc is
  finished or anyone has problems running this program.


@endnode


@node "Installation" "How to install it"

@{b}Installation@{ub}
============

  The installation is very simple:

  Just copy the supplied files to any place you want.

  If you want to use PrlMixerMUI in another language than the built in,
  you have to copy the supplied catalog files to

  Locale:catalogs/<language>

  or to the program directory

  PROGDIR:catalogs/<language>.

  If you've just unpacked the original archive and do not intent to move
  the executable to another directory, PrlMixerMUI is already prepared to
  find its catalog.

  Currently there is only a german translation.

@endnode


@node "Usage" "How to configure and use it"

@{b}Configuration and Usage@{ub}
=======================

  At first start you will see the following window:

   _______________________________________
  |                                      |
  |       Line    Aux1    Aux2    DAC_   |
  | 12dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |  0dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |-12dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |-24dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |  |
  |      |O||O|  |O||O|  |O||O|  |O||O|  |
  |   oo |_||_|  |_||_|  |_||_|  |_||_|  |
  |                                      |
  |______________________________________|


  Here you can set the output levels for each channel left and right
  splitted. Simple.

  There are several menus. Let's first explane "Settings":


     Lock Line
     Lock Aux1
     Lock Aux2
     Lock DAC

  These are checkable items. You can lock and unlock the left/right
  sliders to be able to change the volume seperately.


     Show level

  These checkable menuentry makes the level section visible. Then the
  GUI looks like this:

   ________________________________________________________
  |                                                        |
  |       Line    Aux1    Aux2    DAC_          Level      |
  | 12dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |    ______  ______  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |   |______||______| |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |                    |
  |  0dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |    ______  ______  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |   |______||______| |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |                    |
  |-12dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |    ______  ______  |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |   |______||______| |
  |      | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |                    |
  |-24dB | || |  | || |  | || |  | || |    ______  ______  |
  |      |O||O|  |O||O|  |O||O|  |O||O|   |______||______| |
  |   oo |_||_|  |_||_|  |_||_|  |_||_|                    |
  |                                                        |
  |________________________________________________________|


  Here you can see the selected level as text in decibel.
  Simple too.


  Oups. My time's running away. Let's short explain the prefs
  window which you can open via "Open prefs window" menu entry
  in the preferences menu:


     Line name: - The name that is displayed over the Line level slider.
     Aux1 name: - Same for Aux1 slider.
     Aux2 name: - Aux2 slider.
      DAC name: - DAC slider.

     Reset Prelude on startup: - If selected, the Prelude is resetted
                                 every time PrlMixerMUI is started.



  To manually reset the sound card, you can select "Reset Prelude" from
  the "Prelude" menu.


  For loading, saving and quitting you use the "Project" menu.
  The program saves the slider (volume) settings, all prefs window entries
  the locking of sliders and the showing of the level section.

  I think no more explanation is needed.



@endnode


